FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
20160728 # FEATURES
These `enums` are now available in Appclusvie.Public
* HealthCheckStatusEnum * RoleTypeEnum * TrusteeTypeEnum * CatalogueTypeEnum * GateStatusEnum * GateTypeEnum * EntityBagProtectionLevelEnum * CatalogueStatusEnum
TenantsController Hierarchy API
* added Odata action for IsAcestor * added Odata action for IsParent * added Odata action for IsChild * added Odata action for IsDescendant * added Odata action for IsSelf * added Odata action for IsSibling * added Odata action for IsRelated
# NOTES
Catalogue Visibility
* Added check to hide timewise invalid catalogue items on $expand operations from catalogue
RetryHelper
* Reduced logging * Changed logged func name to caller name
SetSecurityProtocol
* Changed invocation to only apply on global events

biz.dfch.CS.Appclusive.Public ========================
Interfaces, Dtos and Constants of the Appclusive Framework
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
20160805 # FEATURES
Gates
* Added Release method to support releasing gates by name * Added constants for min and max Gate Acquire timeouts * Changed Gate Dtos to derive form BaseDto * Changed BaseEntityCreate to derive from BaseDto * Changed GateAcquire dto, changed WaitTimeout to have a valid default of 1 and changed the max to 60000 (was 5000) * Changed GateAcquireForEntity dto, changed WaitTimeout to have a valid default of 1 and changed the max to 60000 (was 5000) * Changed GateAcquireForEntityKind dto, changed WaitTimeout to have a valid default of 1 and changed the max to 60000 (was 5000)
PowerShell project
* Added project for PoSH scripts
Connectors and Interfaces
* Added Connectors and Interfaces, which allow to define required dependencies between child and parent node * Added Connector Checks on *Nodes*
# BUGFIXES
Gates
* Fixed GateAcquire / Release actions to return false when acquiring or releasing fails (instead of HTTP 400) * Required permission for releasing gates changed to GatesCanDelete
EntityBagsController
* Template action fixed
JobBody
* Added Range validation to only allow valid entities (i.e. >= 1)
FileMessagingClient
* Replaced formatted date time in message name with GUID to avoid overriding of messages because of equal file name
InheritanceManager
* Avoid copying equivalent ACEs on break inheritance
# Notes
ReplicationManager
* Added Replication for BaseEntity * Changed CatalogueManager to use ReplicationManager
UpdateManager
* Removed explicit BaseEntity types with generic T
Appclusive.Products
* New NuGet Package biz.dfch.Appclusive.Products
Gates
* Changed minimum wait timeout to 0 ms
Constants
* Modified Constants.EntityKindId enum to be based on Int64 instead of Int32
StructureMap
* Added Dependency Injection with StructureMap
# Migration Manual * Update RefreshToken, if necessary! ApiGee may has the new Impersonisation Deny Patch.

20160823 # BUGFIXES
* Validation added to Nodes link method to avoid linking Node with itself * Fixed Issue, where Networks were cached over the whole Tenants instead per User, per Tenant
# FEATURES
ScheduledJob * Added Quartz.Net support * Added validation of crontab and quartz expressions * added DataType controller and model * added dynamic data type validation from `DataType` model via compiled assemblies * added `BaseDto` instance creation to set default values from `DefaultValue` attributes * added validation attribute `ValidatePattern` * added validation attribute `ValidateSet` * added validation attribute `ValidateScript` * added validation attribute `Type` * added validation attribute `Increment` * added validation attribute `Unit`
# NOTES
ScheduledJob * Added constants for min, max ranges in model * Added constants for default values in model * Refactored some code for better readability * Added Default JobAction * Added tests
# MIGRATION MANUAL * Adjust `Deploy-Apc.xml` according newest version in [`biz.dfch.PS.Appclusive.Setup`](https://github.com/dfensgmbh/biz.dfch.PS.Appclusive.Setup)

biz.dfch.CS.StateMachine ========================
A simple C# based State Machine that can be configured via State Transitions based on an idea by [Juliet](http://stackoverflow.com/users/40516/juliet) "[Simple state machine example in C#?](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5923767/simple-state-machine-example-in-c)"
# DESCRIPTION
The project contains an extendable StateMachine that defines a few simple states and two conditions ("Continue", "Cancel") that can be used to advance (transition) through that state machine.
When instatiating the StateMachine with the default constructor the following states, conditions and transitions will be set up per default
## States
* Running * InternalErrorState * Completed * Cancelled * Disposed
## Conditions
* Continue * Cancel
## Transitions

Module: biz.dfch.PS.Appclusive.Client
d-fens GmbH, General-Guisan-Strasse 6, CH-6300 Zug, Switzerland
This Microsoft PowerShell module contains Cmdlets to perform various base actions and utility/convenience functions with the our open-source based automation framework "Appclusive".
You can also download this module via [NuGet](http://nuget.org) with [Install-Package biz.dfch.PS.Appclusive.Client](https://www.nuget.org/packages/biz.dfch.PS.Appclusive.Client/)
See http://appclusive.net
Third party (and Microsoft) DLLs are not part of this Apache 2.0 licensed project but are only put here for convenience.
See https://github.com/dfensgmbh/biz.dfch.PS.Appclusive.Client/wiki for a detailed description on how to use the Cmdlets in this module.

* installation base path is '$env:ProgramFiles\WindowsPowerShell\Modules' and can be manually set as input parameter

biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging ==========================
Modules: biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging
d-fens GmbH, General-Guisan-Strasse 6, CH-6300 Zug, Switzerland
This PowerShell module contains Cmdlets that allow to perform logging from your PowerShell functions and code via the Apache Log4Net library.
* You can also download this module via [NuGet](http://nuget.org) with [Install-Package biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging](https://www.nuget.org/packages/biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging/).
* After downloading the package to a directory of your choice (_NOT_ the actual module directory) run the `install.ps1` script in the downloaded folder to copy the files to a directory inside `$ENV:PSModulePath`).
* In case you already have a previous version of this module ( < 1.0.5) in a different module directory you have to remove that module manually.
* In case you update the module in the same directory and the `log4net.dll` is still loaded you might have to restart all the PowerShell sessions to be able to overwrite the file.
* In case you changed the log settings in `biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging.xml`, `Log4netConfiguration.xml` or `log4net.xml` you have to restore the changes as they will get overwritten.
See http://d-fens.ch/2013/01/16/module-biz-dfch-ps-system-logging/ and the [Wiki](https://github.com/dfch/biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging/wiki) for more information.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: 20150326 * Added installer - run install.ps1 to copy the module to a PowerShell module path directory
FeedPackage.Summary: This PowerShell module provides Cmdlets to perform logging from your PowerShell script via log4net to arbitrary log format. Logging can be configured via log4net configuration file.
FeedPackage.Title: biz.dfch.PS.System.Logging

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
20160723 # NOTES
Beginning with this release we will follow the [semver](http://semver.org) convention strictly. This means (amon others) that every breaking change in behaviour of a single Cmdlet will lead to a major version increment of the whole module.
# BREAKING CHANGES
* ConvertFrom-CmdletHelp * renamed `ExcludeDefaultCmdletPrefix` to `IncludeDefaultCmdletPrefix` to better represent the logic behind its use (as a default parameter) * logic stays the same: by default the resulting commands from module do *NOT* include the module prefix
# BUGFIXES
* ConvertFrom-CmdletHelp * fixed conversion error in Cmdlets from -Module parameter * added better exception handling not found cmdlets
# FEATURES
* Get-DataType * added Cmdlet to display available .NET data types and its constructors
* Get-DataType
* added Get-DataType Cmdlet to return type information from loaded assemblies
* Get-Constructor
* changed output from Get-Constructor to display full qualified class name instead of only class name
* Invoke-WithRetry * updated Invoke-WithRetry to throw the last exception upon exceeded retries * re-released the Cmdlet due to a versioning error in the last release (1.1.1)
* Invoke-GenericMethod * added Invoke-GenericMethod Cmdlet to facilitate invocation of generic methods * re-released the Cmdlet due to a versioning error in the last release (1.1.1)
* Set-SslSecurityPolicy * deprecated the TrustAllCertificates switch (default is now 'false') * removed positional parameters * changed delegate for CertificateCallback to inline C# code to remove problem with async PowerShell threads on missing default runspaces * added whatif/confirm message * formatting * added inline help * re-released the Cmdlet due to a versioning error in the last release (1.1.1)
* installation base path is '$env:ProgramFiles\WindowsPowerShell\Modules' and can be manually set as input parameter

let (|None|One|Many|) (x:'a list) = match x with | x when x.Length > 1 -> Many | x when x.Length = 1 -> One | _ -> None
let (|Equal|Different|) = function | v1, v2 when v1 = v2 -> Equal | v1, v2 when v1 <> v2 -> Different | _ -> failwith "unknown"
let (|Positive|Neutral|Negative|) = function | x when x > 0 -> Positive | x when x = 0 -> Neutral | x when x < 0 -> Negative | _ -> failwith "unknown"
